lines.text: One Rocket Charlie, I'm leading your hairspace.
Well, excuse me for still believing in Sunday walks in the park and little babies!

[while patrolling in unmarked patrol car, telling joke]
I cannot lie. I was humping my goat. So, the D.A. says, "But there's more to the story, isn't there, Farmer Brown?"
So, Farmer Brown says, "After I finished humping my goat, the goat turned around and licked my balls." At which point, the judge turned to Farmer Brown and said, "Hey, a good goat will do that."
[Gordon looks at Jimmy with no response]
A good... Aw, come on. Gordy. I had everybody rolling with that this morning.

[smiles]
Yeah, you're sad, man. You're really sad.
